The paper discusses a variant of McEliece's cryptosystem and proposes the use of generalized Reed-Solomon codes. The attack presented in the paper is based on a distinguisher of Reed-Solomon codes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper discusses the security and implementation aspects of the proposed cryptosystem.
